195
00:16:51,025 --> 00:16:54,004
Hello, Batman.

196
00:16:54,028 --> 00:16:56,037
I suppose we've been through all this before.

197
00:16:57,016 --> 00:16:59,007
If it matters, you did catch me off guard.

198
00:16:59,031 --> 00:17:02,022
But that only works the first time.

199
00:17:05,031 --> 00:17:06,020
The New Year's ball.

200
00:17:06,044 --> 00:17:08,015
That's where you've hidden the device.

201
00:17:08,039 --> 00:17:09,021
And when it reaches zero

202
00:17:09,045 --> 00:17:12,036
this city pays for what they took from me.

203
00:17:18,060 --> 00:17:21,062
Only one minute to midnight, Batman.

204
00:17:29,055 --> 00:17:31,072
Ice try, Batman.

205
00:17:32,051 --> 00:17:33,039
Oh, I did not just say that.

206
00:17:33,063 --> 00:17:36,044
Wait, wait, wait. Okay, I got it.

207
00:17:36,068 --> 00:17:40,048
Ice pellet? That's cold, Batman.

208
00:17:40,072 --> 00:17:42,048
Okay, so I'm not so good with quips.

209
00:17:42,072 --> 00:17:45,043
Your deja vu telling you how this fight ends?

210
00:17:45,067 --> 00:17:46,062
Yeah. Not well.

211
00:17:46,086 --> 00:17:49,062
Then let's hope batgirl gets here soon with plan B.

212
00:17:49,086 --> 00:17:52,058
Time's up.

213
00:17:52,082 --> 00:17:54,078
Please..

214
00:17:56,084 --> 00:17:58,071
You can't stop me. It's fate.

215
00:17:58,095 --> 00:18:03,083
I don't believe in fate. I believe in choice.

216
00:18:13,098 --> 00:18:15,076
You and your little toys.

217
00:18:15,100 --> 00:18:17,106
It's adorable, really.

218
00:18:25,124 --> 00:18:27,084
He can mess with time

219
00:18:27,108 --> 00:18:29,131
but he can't be in two places at once.

220
00:18:41,120 --> 00:18:42,131
Hmm.

221
00:18:49,142 --> 00:18:51,152
I totally saw that coming.

222
00:18:54,133 --> 00:18:56,134
Don't make all these innocent people suffer.

223
00:18:56,158 --> 00:18:59,119
But I was innocent, too, Batman.

224
00:18:59,143 --> 00:19:00,138
Where was my justice?

225
00:19:00,162 --> 00:19:02,137
You made a choice 18 years ago

226
00:19:02,161 --> 00:19:04,141
and you have to live with the consequences.

227
00:19:04,165 --> 00:19:06,163
Don't make another mistake.

228
00:19:08,167 --> 00:19:11,135
I don't make mistakes, Batman.

229
00:19:11,159 --> 00:19:13,160
Not anymore.

230
00:19:18,158 --> 00:19:20,162
Let's try that again.

231
00:19:22,168 --> 00:19:24,182
Left jab. Ooh! Oh!

232
00:19:26,171 --> 00:19:28,163
How are you doing that?

233
00:19:28,187 --> 00:19:30,185
Call it deja vu.

234
00:19:50,211 --> 00:19:53,172
Batman! Had a bit of trouble tracking him down.

235
00:19:53,196 --> 00:19:55,194
But..

236
00:20:01,218 --> 00:20:06,186
It's not too late to make the right choice, Francis.

237
00:20:06,210 --> 00:20:08,190
Dad?

238
00:20:08,214 --> 00:20:10,193
What're you doing?

239
00:20:10,217 --> 00:20:12,202
Matt?

240
00:20:12,226 --> 00:20:17,231
- Get out of here! - Four, three, two, one..

241
00:20:41,248 --> 00:20:43,260
Dad..

242
00:20:46,256 --> 00:20:49,250
My son! No!

243
00:20:58,262 --> 00:21:00,259
Oh..

244
00:21:02,265 --> 00:21:04,283
Nooo!

245
00:21:15,288 --> 00:21:19,282
<i>It's not too late to make the right choice, Francis.</i>

246
00:21:32,301 --> 00:21:35,283
How about you, Master Bruce? Any resolutions?

247
00:21:35,307 --> 00:21:39,279
Same as every year, do my part to help Gotham City.

248
00:21:39,303 --> 00:21:43,283
All set, Mr. Pennyworth.

249
00:21:43,307 --> 00:21:45,283
You're a miracle worker, Mr. Grey.

250
00:21:45,307 --> 00:21:49,287
Sure you won't join us for some eggnog?

251
00:21:49,311 --> 00:21:50,331
No, thanks, Mr. Wayne.

252
00:21:51,310 --> 00:21:53,329
I have my own family to get home to.

253
00:21:56,335 --> 00:21:59,341
All done here, son. Let's get going.

254
00:22:01,337 --> 00:22:03,341
Aw, dad!

